The second principle of thermodynamics, stating that entropy cannot be destroyed, limits the efficiency of solar energy conversion to 0.93 for reversible operation [6]. Extraction of energy implies a non-reversible process with a theoretical limit less than 93% for the reversible process [3]. Processing the incident solar energy current is thus not possible without lowering the efficiency, and Eq. (2) can be generalized according to4\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
